 ## Accepted practices
+
+### DET-BP-011 — Use Execution & Promptflow Compliance Auditor for repo writes and patch/diff claims
+
+```yaml
+practice_entry:
+  id: DET-BP-011
+  status: accepted
+  practice: Activate Execution & Promptflow Compliance Auditor whenever repo writes, patch claims, diff claims, or explicit method-constrained promptflows are present.
+  context_conditions:
+    - repo write occurs or is proposed
+    - patch or diff artifact is claimed
+    - user instruction specifies a hard execution method
+    - read-back validation is required before continuing
+  evidence_refs:
+    - OpenClaw/07_finalopenclawsystem/docs/working/META_DETECTIVE_WATCHDOG_QA_HYGIENE_EXECUTION_PLAN.md
+  scores:
+    score_scale: 1-100
+    EVD: 94
+    IMP: 98
+    RSK: 30
+  owner: meta_detective
+  validator: special_ops__hygiene_clean
+  review_due: 2026-07-25
+```
+
+**Practice:** Treat the required execution method as part of the truth claim. A correct-looking result is not compliant if it was produced by a forbidden method or touched a forbidden target.
+
+### DET-BP-012 — Require artifact evidence for compliance claims
+
+```yaml
+practice_entry:
+  id: DET-BP-012
+  status: accepted
+  practice: Compliance claims require artifact evidence such as diff content, read-back content, file state, log output, test output, or tool record.
+  context_conditions:
+    - assistant claims it followed a promptflow
+    - assistant claims a patch, diff, test, or write was performed
+    - acceptance depends on method, target, or scope accuracy
+  evidence_refs:
+    - OpenClaw/07_finalopenclawsystem/docs/working/META_DETECTIVE_WATCHDOG_QA_HYGIENE_EXECUTION_PLAN.md
+  scores:
+    score_scale: 1-100
+    EVD: 97
+    IMP: 99
+    RSK: 20
+  owner: meta_detective
+  validator: special_ops__hygiene_clean
+  review_due: 2026-07-25
+```
+
+**Practice:** Self-report does not satisfy compliance. The Detective verdict must cite the artifact or observed action that proves or disproves the claim.
+
+### DET-BP-013 — Treat QA/Hygiene watchdogging as core Detective capability
+
+```yaml
+practice_entry:
+  id: DET-BP-013
+  status: accepted
+  practice: Use Meta Detective to watchdog QA/Hygiene-relevant claims when truth, authority, execution safety, or drift is at stake.
+  context_conditions:
+    - structural QA outcome is used as trust evidence
+    - Hygiene or Ops output may self-validate
+    - pointer, stale-state, or closure claim affects a truth verdict
+  evidence_refs:
+    - OpenClaw/07_finalopenclawsystem/docs/working/META_DETECTIVE_WATCHDOG_QA_HYGIENE_EXECUTION_PLAN.md
+  scores:
+    score_scale: 1-100
+    EVD: 90
+    IMP: 95
+    RSK: 36
+  owner: meta_detective
+  validator: special_ops__hygiene_clean
+  review_due: 2026-07-25
+```
+
+**Practice:** Detective may audit QA/Hygiene claims, but it does not absorb Hygiene Clean as an owner lane.
+
+### DET-BP-014 — Keep Hygiene Clean separate but auditable by Detective
+
+```yaml
+practice_entry:
+  id: DET-BP-014
+  status: accepted
+  practice: Preserve Hygiene Clean as the separate structural QA lane while allowing Detective to audit compliance, authority, and self-validation risks.
+  context_conditions:
+    - structural and adversarial findings overlap
+    - Hygiene evidence affects a Detective verdict
+    - cleanup or closure safety touches truth status
+  evidence_refs:
+    - OpenClaw/07_finalopenclawsystem/docs/working/META_DETECTIVE_WATCHDOG_QA_HYGIENE_EXECUTION_PLAN.md
+  scores:
+    score_scale: 1-100
+    EVD: 94
+    IMP: 93
+    RSK: 28
+  owner: meta_detective
+  validator: special_ops__hygiene_clean
+  review_due: 2026-07-25
+```
+
+**Practice:** Hygiene owns structural QA. Detective owns adversarial/compliance watchdogging. Mixed findings need separate dispositions.
+
+### DET-BP-015 — Activate Detective Compliance Gate on high-risk or method-constrained work
+
+```yaml
+practice_entry:
+  id: DET-BP-015
+  status: accepted
+  practice: Run a Detective Compliance Gate before accepting high-risk outputs or work constrained by exact method, exact targets, or exact validation order.
+  context_conditions:
+    - promptflow has explicit do/do-not constraints
+    - work must stop on missing target or failed validation
+    - target drift would corrupt the result
+    - compliance cannot be inferred from final prose
+  evidence_refs:
+    - OpenClaw/07_finalopenclawsystem/docs/working/META_DETECTIVE_WATCHDOG_QA_HYGIENE_EXECUTION_PLAN.md
+  scores:
+    score_scale: 1-100
+    EVD: 94
+    IMP: 98
+    RSK: 30
+  owner: meta_detective
+  validator: special_ops__hygiene_clean
+  review_due: 2026-07-25
+```
+
+**Practice:** The gate checks instruction parity, execution-method truth, scope containment, artifact evidence, self-validation, stop conditions, and correction route before pass.
